Interrupting yourself can be a protection mechanism ⛑️

Do you ever notice yourself wanting to say something, but fear it’ll come out “wrong” as you’re saying it, so you edit yourself as you speak?

When you interrupt yourself, you subconsciously tell yourself that what you’re saying isn’t worthy of being heard.

I notice myself doing this sometimes. I’ll preface something with disclaimers I think I need to include to protect myself from being misunderstood, or rubbing someone the wrong way. 

But if I know my intentions are good, I’m coming from a loving place, and I want to be heard, there is no reason to correct myself as I’m speaking.

Even if it doesn’t come out perfect, at least I know I’m valuing my voice. And the more I do it, the easier it gets.

As humans, we don’t operate with a script in front of us 📝

It makes sense to always want to say the “right” thing, but you do not need to edit yourself down.

Your truth is the “right thing” 🎙️

If things feel heavy, or exciting, or uneasy, and you just want to be heard…

You are allowed to speak up.
You are allowed to take up space.

Ultimately, you decide the value your words have. 

I invite you to notice the next time this happens, and see if you can lean into the discomfort of saying something that you really want to say, but might be an edge for you.

Notice how it feels to hear your own voice, to be heard, and to have your true words fill the space you’re in 🌬️

Be kind and gentle with yourself afterwards.

It is truly a brave thing to speak up.

Without correcting ourselves all the time, we clear up a channel for what we really want to say to come through. And there’s so much power in that. 💪❤️
.
.
.

#vulnerabilitycodes #powerofvulnerability #speakup #speakyourtruth #yourwordsmatter #emotionalwellnesscoach #coach

✨Reconnect with your why & make room for MAGIC✨

Being laser-focused on a goal is wildly admirable

And…

It’s important to stay true to your “why” 

Rather than blindly forging ahead without checking in with yourself once in a while

Ask yourself:

💌 “What is it that I want?”

💌 “Why do I want this?”

💌 “Am I open to it happening in a different way than I am envisioning?”

💌 “Can I make space to receive even more?”

Your permissioning is a prayer.

The Universe will meet you halfway ✨

Yes, it is honorable to stay focused on your path

And also…

See if you can let yourself open up to life’s surprise & delight 🎁

Keep your vision clear and wide so the mystery can co-create with you 

You are worthy of a big dream turned real ❤️

Always rooting for you,
Katie

Last week in Sedona, I finally let an old part of me go 🏜️

A part that was so worried about what others thought.

A part that felt like she needed to say yes to everything and be consistently busy in order to belong.

A part that so desperately wanted to let go, but didn’t know for sure what was on the other side of trust…which made it even harder to release.

The tools I usually utilize for release — writing, talking, turning it all into art — these were not the answer this time.

Instead, I found release in my voice through song and sound 🎶

Through my body in movement 💃

Through breathwork 🫁

Through venturing into the shamanic underworld of my soul, and finally acknowledging what was hidden underneath layers of fear…

💎The desire to dream big without needing to apologize or know how I’m going to get there

💎A balanced state of bliss that knew everything was going to be okay

💎A pure state of bravery that painted wings so grand I could fly anywhere my heart desired

Once I finally surrendered, I realized I didn’t have to dig

I just have to let go.

There is so much strength in surrender.

Once I stopped holding on the old, I began to feel the energy of the new

And that is more powerful than any answer I could get, any clear vision of the next step.

The next level is here, and I’m ready. 🎯

~~~

When I think about what I want to share with the world, the feeling of “I don’t know where to begin” overwhelms me.

Years of collecting musings, curiosities, observations, and wonderment…how can I encapsulate that in something that is a “starting off point”?

This is what keeps me from moving forward. The details. The needing to do it “right”

What would make the most sense? What would be the most wise? What would most people resonate with?

And for a moment, letting the mountain of perfectionism and structure melt away…

Choosing to step away from this dump truck of wisdom that has been collecting holy downloads for years and years…

Just so I can see what’s here, now.

The simplicity of being. What is that right now?A pause. A breath. Listening to what’s around me.

Ahhhh. There it is.

The energy of spaciousness. Enoughness within expansion. Elevated wholeness.

I can tap into a whole new level of being when I stop doing.

The essence of presence.

White noise wisdom.

Truth lives here…uncovered by the embellishment of what we should be, or what we should say

A wealth of wisdom inspired by our body, raw and unedited, purely connected to the root of all that is.

When we peel back the layers, take a deep breath, and let ourselves unfold…

That’s where we can actually see what’s here.

And that’s a great place to start.

🏁

📸: @livingnectar

✨Choosing bravery✨

Upon finally deciding it’s time to go through my journals to share some of my writing…

I froze.

I was so overwhelmed by all the things I had written, musings and downloads from different stages of my life

I couldn’t figure out where to begin

A part of me was afraid to even go through them because often I can get pulled into the energy of what I was feeling at the time, and that felt heavy

This is not to say that what I’ve written is groundbreaking, world-changing, and will no doubt change your life forever…

But it came directly from my heart. Vulnerable scribbles on a page that have helped me process through so many dense feelings and detailed moments, light and dark…

That have hardly seen the light of day.

I’ve kept them so close to my heart that I find it difficult to turn it over to show the world

The desire to is deep, but the resistance is strong.

And still, I’m deciding to be brave anyway and share as I grow.

Now, I could have just shared my writing and not written about writing. I see the redundancy, don’t worry.

But I also wanted to shine a light on how, what we share on here and in the world doesn’t always come easy.

We can post a comment, doubt click to like a photo…but what we don’t always see is how challenging it might have been for the person to share it, or how important it truly is to them.

It might have been…
🌷a significant catalyst for their growth
🌷something that changed their life that they wanted us all to know as well
🌷something that they worked on for weeks or months that’s far beyond what social media shows
🌷something they’ve been sitting on for a long time, terrified to share because of the weight of vulnerability and honesty

But they decided to share it. And that shows SO much bravery.

It’s not always easy to share, or be vulnerable, or just be a human on the internet (or in real life)

But we share, because it’s worth it.

It not only connects us to each other, but it connects us deeper to ourselves. We are mirrors of one another. The vulnerability of the human experience matters.

I’m choosing to share.

And I hope you do too.

More to come ❤️

📸: @livingnectar

I remember when I first sat for tea at a women’s retreat. I thought, “what’s the big deal? What’s so profound about tea?”

2 hours and 10 pages of poetry later…I stopped asking questions.

As I sipped this old, potent tea, I learned to listen. I learned to be still. I learned to let the simplicity of it all become a portal into whatever was calling me during each ceremony, and step forward with trust.

I fell in love immediately 🤍🍃

Since that first tea ceremony 2 years ago, I’ve sat with tea nearly every day. It is a ritual I have felt most aligned with, and my love for the practice has only deepened and expanded from the center of my heart.

The entire process of tea ceremony is true magnificence.

Purifying your space, cleaning the bowls, setting up the tea stage, honoring the tea, the guests, and yourself 🫖

The reverence you place into this ritual can become a bridge to carry reverence into your daily life.

Reverence is easy with Tea 

There isn’t a certain amount of information to learn or understand in order to “get it”

You just drink Tea ☕️

Sometimes you can even just smell Tea, or set her in front of you, watching her steam rise + dance, and you will “get it”
And you will continue to “get it”
Each time you sit with her.

The greatest conversationalist
who needn’t say a word.

Simple. Sweet. Profound.

Life reflected in a bowl of water & leaves 🍃

Happy International Tea Day, my friends 🍵

May you take sips of life from a full cup 💚

Special thanks to @becomingmedicine for introducing me to Tea and being an incredible Tea-cher to myself and so many others. You are truly an inspiration 🙏

I did this mirror practice a few days ago, and it created a shift in me that still feels strong.
✨
I had been feeling a bit disconnected, ungrounded, and behind in my goals.
✨
Often I can give myself a little pep talk, or write it out, but this time I could sense that my body was craving an embodiment practice. Something that could be felt, trusted, and sustained.
✨
Looking myself in the eye, I spent time acknowledging what I’ve been struggling with, reminding myself of my accomplishments, expressing gratitude for the times I acted in a way that aligned with my values, and apologized to and forgave myself for the times that I didn’t.
✨
I didn’t expect to get emotional during this practice, but when the tears started to fall, I realized how deeply I needed this.
✨
Not from someone else, but from me
✨
Face to face, heart to heart, truly seeing myself in my own experience and honoring right where I am, so I can take the next step with a full heart knowing that I’ve got me in my corner.
✨
After this tender practice I put on some music and moved my body in celebration, to let the energy integrate. Fully embodied joy, a tender knowingness that everything is going to be okay, even in the mystery.
✨
Offering myself an embrace that felt more true than ever before.
✨
It feels vulnerable to share this intimate practice with you.
But I know that if it helped me, it might help you too.
✨
Listen closely to when your heart or your body might have something to share with you, and allow yourself to be creative in however you choose to set the space for it.
✨
The more permission you allow yourself to connect, process, and be, the more avenues you create to access the most potent joy that is available to us in this life.
✨
And we all deserve that ❤️

Life doesn’t have to be a choice of “this OR that”
it can be an “AND”

Being mindful of where this energy is being fueled from is important.

I love being a coach, and building my business/brand 🖇️
AND
I love being an artist, dancer, and performer who is passionate about movement & expression 💃

I love staying home and working on my business 👩‍💻
AND
I love playing and dancing with my friends, working on creative projects, and performing at events 🦄

When I limit myself to needing to choose which cup to fill in my life, I find myself operating from the energy of lack…

“I can’t do it all”
“I don’t have enough time”
“I’m so behind”
“I’m too busy”

and suddenly, nothing I do feels like it’s enough.

But when I shift my energy into “the possibilities of what I can enjoy right now are limitless”…

I’m able to open myself up to flow again 🌀

I can say no to some things, and still love it. Honoring my boundaries so that love can lead first.

I can intentionally make room in my life so I can enjoy even more

I can pay attention to what brings me joy, and choose them from a place of availability.

Doing & enjoying don’t always go hand in hand.
Sometimes you’ve got to lessen the do so you can enjoy ⚖️

I can still give my all. But I need to give myself a chance to have all to give.

Sacred pauses are necessary to zoom out and remember why we love something, so we can fill up our tank.

So I don’t need to choose 1 thing, or worry about needing to “do it all”

I can decide to follow what brings me joy, and from this overflow, none of my cups will ever be empty 🍵

Thank you for capturing these photos while I was smack dab in the joy zone @derekgonewild 📸

✨You’re allowed to ask for what you want…

At some point in our lives many of us accepted the story that we need to wait for things to come to us

Stepping up to the plate and speaking up about what we want might be considered selfish, bratty, or inappropriate

“Stay in your lane and wait your turn”

I’m here to remind you that this is not true 🚫

You can speak up and ask for what you want. You can even demand it.

Everything you desire is available to you. What you want is wanting you back.

Whether that’s an opportunity, a way of communicating, treatment, or a life shift…

You can make the first move

And this will tell the Universe, “I’m ready. I’m serious. I’m out here making moves”

And the Universe will listen, and respond to that 🪄

It might feel uncomfortable at first, being honest about what you want and expressing that to others. But they might not know. And it’s up to you to make it known.

That is POWERFUL

We are all here to create a life we are proud to live, designing it in our own way. And the people who love you want to help you get there. So speaking up benefits everyone

Patience is a virtue

AND

Life is happening NOW 🙌

So it would be wise to step forward in the direction of what you want and what you want your life to feel like, so that life begins to kickstart and continues to flow.

It starts with you ❤️

✨Somatic Practice: shaking off the excess of what no longer serves you/isn’t yours

This is a practice I do after my coaching calls. Before checking my phone, sending emails, or any other tasks, I get up and move my body💃

It’s important to do this not just for my own well being, but in service of my other clients, my loved ones I spend time with, and anyone I interact with throughout the day

Coming back to my center through this exercise isn’t just helpful, it’s FUN! It reminds me that my body is so wise…and so silly at the same time.

And by giving myself this permission, that permission flows into every single thing I do for the rest of the day.

Sometimes after a phone call, meeting, or being social, there’s some lingering energy that doesn’t need to be kept in our body.

We might sit on the couch and watch TV, go back to work, or even have panicked responses due to an overloaded nervous system 😓

Animals shake when they need to recalibrate. In stressful situations, after a nap, or when they’re excited

As humans, sometimes we forget to recalibrate after being in a space that requires so much of our energy. 

Our bodies know what’s up! And having a practice that allows you to call back your energy and shake off everything else can be incredibly supportive AND fun!

Try this practice out next time you feel you’re holding onto something that feels like a lot, or might not even be yours

And let me know how it goes 😊

Would love to see your wiggles!

Tea is my greatest love, and greatest teacher 🌿

Each time I sit for tea, I am reminded that I might be over-complicating things. I just need to get back to basics.

➡️Do I need to do a million things today? NO.
➡️Do I need to have a profound moment or groundbreaking idea during this time? NO.
➡️Is sitting for 3-5 bowls of tea an unproductive use of my time? Absolutely NOT.

Will tea accept me exactly as I am, even if I’m experiencing anxiety or overthinking?

100%

Tea gives you permission to be just as you are.

Allowing anything to come up, and letting it go

Savoring the nectar as you sip it in, listening to any whispered messages, feeling your own roots grounding down.

Nature grows and thrives without needing to consult with us

So how can we allow this of ourselves?

Just letting ourselves grow, without forcing, feverishly thinking of what we must “improve” or “fix”, or needing things to be different.

Trusting in the progress of it all, and letting yourself enjoy the present

Hot water & leaves. Back to basics.

This is how we remember ❤️

Imagine how life would feel if you completely took self-doubtful language out of your vocabulary ❌

I realized this morning how much I speak about what I “can’t” do, what feels hard for me, and how much farther I have to go with my goals

This feeds my desire to fix things. Figuring out what I like and don’t like, what I need to do more of to be more xyz…

And it’s harder to take action from this place of limitation.

Being honest about how we feel is one thing

But it’s important to notice when what we say becomes what we believe

Being careful not to create an even longer loop between our limiting thoughts and words

Our words hold SO much power.

So I’m going to make a point to stop myself when I speak from a place of “I can’t do this” or “it’s too hard” or “I’m not far enough”

…and instead, just take action.

Because it’s the action where limiting beliefs can be erased, and evidence for why our desires are worth pursuing can be created

Feel free to join me in this practice ❤️

I’ve encountered so many people with a fear of being “too much” — myself included 🙋‍♀️

And this often comes up right before a big opportunity

Right before hanging out with a new friend, getting a new job, or taking a big risk

Inspiration and excitement build up, and then BAM — fear comes right after it

“What if I come off too strong?”
“What if I ask too many questions?”
“What if I talk about myself too highly and it sounds like I’m bragging?”

And all of a sudden, our minds choose comfort over the leap we wanted to take.

Choosing playing small over taking up space.

If we zoom out, we can see that we’re not doing anyone any favors by holding back

The worst that can happen is someone not aligning with you. And if that’s the case, so what? For another person, job, or situation, you’ll be the gold shining star that they’ve been looking everywhere for

So it’s WORTH it to shine your brightest, be your most. Share that idea, be excited, feel your feelings. That’s YOU. And the world needs and loves you, exactly as you are. Full throttle.

Life is too short to fit into someone else’s box

And you’re too vibrant to hold yourself back from sharing your magic.

Pretty please, next time you find yourself wanting to hold back, choose to step forward instead. Be a lot. We’re ready for it ❤️

Slowing down can give you the codes to getting things done 🐢

This may sound simple, but in the midst of overwhelm, sometimes simplicity doesn’t feel accessible.

Often when I set my mind to something, I feel like I need to do more, learn more, remember more…

I need to check ALL the boxes (and the sub-boxes too!) so I can get that gold star in Life School ⭐️

But in the midst of this…I lose control. I’m out of balance. My heart isn’t in it, and my mind is 20 steps ahead so my body doesn’t know what to do *right now*

And really, right now is all that matters. This is where change can be planted, and we can tend to that seed.

I’ve found the most success in slowing down, taking a deep breath, and focusing on the following things:

1. Bringing myself back into my body (via touch, sound, or breath)

2. Asking my body what it needs most in this moment (I.e. movement, sunshine, a journaling break)

3. Offering my focus to the task in front of me, and trusting that’s enough 

1 million half-assed tasks done with an overwhelmed body & mind won’t get us very far (and may result in shame instead)

Few tasks done with a present & nurtured body & mind…that’s the ticket to sustainable progress 📈

And often, once I slow down, I can hear my heart more clearly. My heart always knows what to do. I just need to slow down to actually hear those messages ❣️

Slow down. Check in. Take a deep breath. Start with what’s here and know you can take a break if your mind’s running off on you.

Remember: 
This is not a waste of time. It’s an integral part of your growth, and you deserve to be present for it. ❤️

I’d like to think I’m a pretty self-aware person, but sometimes I use that to avoid admitting things to myself.

It feels like, if I did admit it, I’d be weak, or found out, or a brand new pile of “things to heal” would be dropped on my lap

And who has time for that?

But on the contrary, admitting things to ourselves about how we respond to life isn’t weak at all, it can actually give us the tools we need to face it head-on and respond in a way that helps, rather than hurts us

And this is SO much more healing than avoiding the topic altogether and acting like it doesn’t exist.

There’s no need to act like the big strong hero who doesn’t need to dig deeper.

You might not even need to dig as deep as you’re dreading. It might be waiting for you right at the surface

As if to say “I’m right here! Thank you for acknowledging me! Now here’s exactly how we can heal this…”

When we actually give ourselves the time and attention we deserve, we can uncover SO many tools that we can use to heal, strengthen, and grow

And that starts with being honest with ourselves 🙌

Vulnerability has felt mucky, y’all.

Lately, it’s been something I’ve felt comfortable talking about, but not so comfortable practicing on my own.

I’ve found myself holding back when wanting DEEPLY to share. But instead, I’d hide.

Though being vulnerable is never really a comfortable practice, it’s always medicinal. When practiced in a safe space, even more so.

More specifically, with myself.

A few weeks ago, my fiancé went on a retreat. 

We’re not often apart. So I felt some fear come up. But I took this as an opportunity to land back into myself. Treat myself as a priority. Strengthen the foundation I operate from, since I’ve noticed lately it needs some care.

I received a clear message from my body, telling me that all I needed to do was sit with myself, 3x a day

I call it “bookmarking” 🔖

Instead of running away from myself, I anchor in. ⚓️

Morning, mid-day and before bed. I close my eyes, and breathe. Connect with what comes up within me. Let it be there.

Without trying to change it, heal it, or fix it. Just let my body know I’m here, and I’m listening.

I started this 2 weeks ago, and have been practicing ever since.

And I’m not exaggerating when I say it’s one of the most profoundly effective self-love practices I’ve done in a LONG time.

When I let myself just be, without immediately forcing a healing modality, I can actually hear my body speaking its needs to me.

I feel more grounded, like I’ve arrived back into myself. And if I ever waver throughout the day, or feel a little untethered, it’s a short journey back to me, because I’ve left breadcrumbs to find myself again.

Right in my body.

I share this with you to remind you that practices to make you feel at home within yourself do not have to be complicated. Simplicity holds SO much power.

Sometimes all you need to do is sit, close your eyes, and breathe. Let that be enough to come back to yourself.

You’re never too far away. 🏠

Celebration dance because: I swam in the ocean today! 🌊

This is a big deal to me

The ocean intimidates me sometimes. I often stand at the shore and study the flow of the water to determine the best time to enter before the waves eat me

Wondering when it’ll be “safe” to jump in

But really, the ocean is going to do whatever tf she wants to do. That’s why I LOVE her

And swimming in the ocean takes a lot of trust

A lot of “go with the flow”

And waiting for things to be “safe enough” is only going to keep me in survival mind and hold me back forever

So I chose to listen to my body this morning and take the plunge. Do the thing that scared me and take the lesson that came from it

Small things like this are SO worthy of celebration. Because they’re not actually small at all. They show us what we’re made of 💪

And if we only celebrate the big steps, we don’t see the incredible impact the small progressive steps offer

And we are worthy of seeing each step as a celebratory achievement because we’re aligning with who we are and what we are capable of 🙌

I’ll offer you these questions to ask yourself:

🌱 What’s something you can do today that scares you, but your body is telling you to go for it?

🌱 Can you let yourself take a small step, and celebrate yourself for it?

Celebrating you exactly where you are 💕🎉

Letting go of control isn’t as easy as “just surrender!” 🛑

I’ve been learning this lesson all my life.

And it feels like I’m setting myself up to fail when I force myself to surrender, and I just can’t.

In comes the shame. And then we start the cycle over again.

Recently, I’ve come to the discovery that the piece I wasn’t seeing in between control and surrender is:

✨F L E X I B I L I T Y✨

After years of having a controlling protection mechanism run the show, it’s normal for it to be challenging when it comes to “just letting go”

🌀But what if instead of creating an iron-clad schedule with outlines of what could go wrong, I could just be flexible?

🌀What if I decided to trust that whatever happens, I’m equipped to handle it?

🌀What if I trusted my team of support to have my back or take the reins if it came to that?

Life comes in and teaches us these things in real time. And we get to show up for the lesson.

I definitely perked up for this one and knew it was worth sharing ✨

If you struggle to let go of control, you’re not alone. Give yourself lots of compassion — you likely learned that’s what you needed to do to keep yourself safe. If it feels like it’s no longer serving you, ask yourself:

🪢How can I release my grip just a little bit?

🔮Can I allow space in this situation for magic to pour through and for Life to surprise me?

📓Am I willing to learn something from this experience, rather than letting this story run the show?

Remember to give yourself grace. Growing requires a lot of patience. The progress is always worth it.

It’s been a hot minute since I flowed for my own enjoyment

I haven’t felt connected to my hoop in a while. And it makes me sad when that happens. It’s something that has brought me joy for SO long and it scares me when I don’t feel the joy that I used to.

But I’ve said it before, and I’ll say it again:

The flow aaaaaaalways comes back 🌀

That’s the whole point. It flows with us, as we flow with our own life and growth.

I’m happy I can always trust that this form of play will always be here. That my heart is in it and that will never change. The love I have for flow, play, and movement is not directly correlated with the inspiration that comes in waves. If I depend on that inspiration to be there all the time, I would suffocate the play it holds, and I would get burnt out.

So I cherish the moments inspiration and the desire to express in these ways come to visit. Even if they don’t last forever, I know that desire will always come back.

If you’ve been feeling a certain way because you haven’t felt inspired to do something you “used to” or “normally” love to do, you’re not alone. There are seasons to our creativity. Know that the inspiration and desire to get back into it will return. See if you can keep a space warm in your heart to welcome it back when it’s time. And trust the process you’re in. ❤️

Thank you @humananimalofficial for capturing this moment of pure joy with my hoop. I was right in the bliss zone and I’m so grateful I have a momento of this moment 😍

WORKSHOP ~ ‘Cacao & Choreo’
This class is all about hooping with a partner, because hooping is ALWAYS better with friends. In this workshop, we’ll be learning a partner hoop routine that will emphasize choreography dynamics such as levels, mirroring, canons and more. Before moving into our choreo, we’ll ground in with cacao to open our hearts and root into a sacred, playful space. Once we’re dropped in, we’ll pair up with a partner and move through a series of connection exercises that inspire trust and connection. Partner work isn’t just about learning moves together, it’s about getting into an authentic flow with your partner that can be felt by the audience. From this place of connection and playfulness, we’ll learn a choreographed partner hoop routine that will begin with a single hoop and evolve into two hoops. You’ll discover how you can stylize the routine based on musicality, theme, and overall vibe. You’ll walk away with a routine to weave into your performances, and a deepened connection with your partner!

Even as life has gotten busy lately, I’m so grateful I’ve had moments sprinkled throughout that remind me to stay present
✨
It’s tough to spend time off our phones these days. I’ll admit, it’s an addiction of mine. Christian and I went on a trip to Joshua Tree and I wanted to make sure I stayed off my phone. The idea alone felt crunchy. What if I needed to respond to something immediately? How will I get updates on things?
✨
But when we were there, doing the things we loved to do, and doing them together…it wasn’t hard at all to be off my phone (with the exception of photos). Often the idea of something seems a lot scarier than it actually is.
✨
Plus, the internet at our Airbnb wasn’t working. It was meant to be 🙃
✨
All this to say, it’s not so hard to be present when you focus on doing things that make you happy, with the people that make you feel safe AND the ones who make you want to do the things you love to do. I’m always trying to be better at putting my phone down rather than picking up when I’m uncomfortable. There’s so much of life to be rooted into, and I don’t want to miss it 🌱

Love you to the moon @humananimalofficial ❤️ thank you for always being patient with me in my processes, keeping me accountable, and reminding me to give myself grace 🙏

For a long time I wanted to be swept off my feet and taken on adventures. I once dated a man who promised to take me camping, which I had been wanting for so long. Our relationship ended before we ever went.

From then on I told myself that if I wanted to do something, be taken somewhere, or have a certain experience, I’d make it happen myself. 

I listen intently to my heart. I know when I feel off balance. I know how to check in on my needs.

Whenever life gets chaotic or my mind gets too loud, I take myself to the beach. Sip tea. Read my book. Let myself be held by the earth. 

I often get lost in wanting someone to love the things I love, just as much as I love them. Slow moments in big natural spaces. Riding the poetic waves of life. I want someone to share these moments with me.

But sometimes I want this so badly that I forget the fact that I wanted it in the first place. And I get to give it to me. No one else needs to be responsible for that. 

Waiting for someone else to take me to these places creates the belief that only another person can make this possible. Taking myself there shows that I can create this reality, and everything else becomes magnetized to this energy.

We create what we want, and the universe responds accordingly ✨

What have you been wanting that you can take steps towards making it happen for yourself today?

Show yourself that it’s possible 💕

My name’s Katie and I’m an artist 🦋

I’m a fire dancer, jewelry maker, painter, and writer.

I’ve dealt with imposter syndrome, feelings of unworthiness, artistic resistance, and self-doubt more times than I can count

It’s kept me from going (or even dreaming) BIG because I’ve always felt like being big isn’t safe. I needed to know how to do everything before doing it

And in the moments where I didn’t let fear hold me back but rather walked headfirst into the mystery with the fear in tow, I’ve experienced the most joy, transformation, and bliss than I ever thought possible

So I want to help as many artists feel like they can do the big scary things too ✨

Even if that’s just posting their art online

Or as big as submitting their project to a reputable brand

Or even just feeling worthy as an artist (this is an important one)

I know how difficult it can be to put yourself out there and be the artist you deeply desire to be

Often times (let’s say 90-99% of the time) it’s ourselves who are holding us back from the happiness available to us.

It feels scary. Impossible. Too big.

But the desire doesn’t go away.

Years of support from mentors, coaches, and therapists have helped me see and appreciate my own bigness, and how necessary that is for me to claim my own joy as an artist

And now I want to offer it to you✨

Keep watching this space as I have an exciting announcement coming up ❤️

I am honored to be serving Tea in the jungle at @oasishoopretreat in October 2024 🌿

Imagine the pure bliss of sitting in soft, sweet silence as the warm Costa Rican air tickles your skin, and jungle creatures glitter the air with their whispers. Saying a gentle “hello” to what arises within you as you sip pure living tea alongside others who are just as present in their journey as you are in yours ☕️🧘🏻‍♀️🌴

Tea came into my life in 2021 and has been with me ever since. She is a wise teacher, humble leader, and patient friend.

I sit with Tea to connect with the Earth, with my heart, and with the energies that often feel too abstract to define in daily life, but become easily experienced — wordless and clear — in the presence of Tea and the stillness of you. 🕊️

During a tea ceremony, you may feel inspired to write, cry, meditate, dream, or simply just sip the tea. 🍵

While there are no psychoactive properties in Tea, she does take you on a gentle journey within yourself. 🌀

I truly cannot wait for you to experience Tea for yourself. I am so grateful to be able to share my favorite practice with those who are called to sit in sweet silence with the earth ❤️

Who is the artist you desire to become?✨

Often I’ll fall asleep with every intention to wake up and create. But if I wake up and don’t “feel” like creating anymore, I’ll let resistance hold me back.

And then shame eats me alive.

The question I’ve begun to ask myself that has strengthened my artistic devotion ten-fold is:

✨“Is this the kind of artist I want to be?”

We get to decide who we are. We create it every day. We can change course, make adjustments, and re-commit ourselves to a new way whenever we please.

So if I ever find myself up against resistance, I’ll remind myself out loud:

“I’m the kind of artist who creates because she loves it, no matter what her mood is.”

or

“I’m the kind of artist who creates even when she’s scared.”

And my actions begin to follow suit.

Of course, I have days where I need to rest. And in this case, I’ll remind myself,

“I’m the kind of artist who deserves to rest and recharge her artistic battery.”

and

“I’m the kind of artist who doesn’t shame herself for taking 1 day off. I’m allowing this to be a day of artful rest.”

The days that used to feel like I’m letting myself and my work down, become days filled with compassion and understanding of my process.

This reframe has allowed me to unclench and let myself, and my art, breathe. I can see a difference in what I create, the energy of it all has expanded.

And so I invite you to ask yourself:

“Who is the artist I desire to become?”

“What kinds of days do they have? How do they redirect when resistance comes to visit?”

“How do they practice compassion and devotion with themselves and their work?”

Let it become a gentle practice. See how things shift. And let me know if this is helpful to you ❤️
